listManagement::buildInsertUpdateString()

Description
    private string listManagement::buildInsertUpdateString()
    Builds a valid MySQL update string, iterating through $this->fields and concatenating $this->engine->cleanPost['MYSQL'][$I["field"]."_insert"]."'" to a 
    local variable, $temp. $I is initialized in a foreach loop and represents an iteration of the array $this->fields.

Return Values
    Returns a string containing the combined fields of $this->engine->openDB->escape($I["field"]) and $this->engine->cleanPost['MYSQL'][$I["field"]."_".$row], comma delimited.

Examples
    <?php
	...
	$sql = sprintf("UPDATE %s SET %s WHERE ID='%s'",
	    $this->engine->openDB->escape($this->table),
	    $this->buildUpdateString($row[0]),
	    $row[0]
	);
	...
    ?>

See Also
    listManagement::buildUpdateString()
